comment:
* Description of the response of a setup data call connection request.
 *
 * @hide

variables.name: LINK_STATUS_INACTIVE
variables.comment: Indicates the data connection is inactive.

variables.name: LINK_STATUS_DORMANT
variables.comment: Indicates the data connection is active with physical link dormant.

variables.name: LINK_STATUS_ACTIVE
variables.comment: Indicates the data connection is active with physical link up.

methods.name: public int getCause()
methods.comment: * @return Data call fail cause. {@link DataFailCause#NONE} indicates no error.

methods.name: public int getSuggestedRetryTime()
methods.comment: * @return The suggested data retry time in milliseconds.

methods.name: public int getId()
methods.comment: * @return The unique id of the data connection.

methods.name: public List<LinkAddress> getAddresses()
methods.comment: * @return A list of addresses of this data connection.

methods.name: public List<InetAddress> getDnsAddresses()
methods.comment:
* @return A list of DNS server addresses, e.g., "192.0.1.3" or
     * "192.0.1.11 2001:db8::1". Empty list if no dns server addresses returned.

methods.name: public List<InetAddress> getGatewayAddresses()
methods.comment:
* @return A list of default gateway addresses, e.g., "192.0.1.3" or
     * "192.0.1.11 2001:db8::1". Empty list if the addresses represent point to point connections.

methods.name: public List<InetAddress> getPcscfAddresses()
methods.comment:
* @return A list of Proxy Call State Control Function address via PCO (Protocol Configuration
     * Option) for IMS client.

methods.name: public int getMtu()
methods.comment:
* @return MTU (maximum transmission unit) in bytes received from network. Zero or negative
     * values means network has either not sent a value or sent an invalid value.
     * @deprecated For IRadio 1.5 and up, use {@link #getMtuV4} or {@link #getMtuV6} instead.

methods.name: public int getMtuV4()
methods.comment:
* This replaces the deprecated method getMtu.
     * @return MTU (maximum transmission unit) in bytes received from network, for IPv4.
     * Zero or negative values means network has either not sent a value or sent an invalid value.

methods.name: public int getMtuV6()
methods.comment:
* @return MTU (maximum transmission unit) in bytes received from network, for IPv6.
     * Zero or negative values means network has either not sent a value or sent an invalid value.

methods.name: public void writeToParcel(Parcel dest, int flags)

methodNames: public void writeToParcel(Parcel dest, int flags)
